{"/service/ndnp/mimtptc/batch_mimtptc_clare_ver03/data/sn97063233/0041418800A/1945081401/0539.xml":{"full_text":"r\n\\T\nThey Both Endured a Lot For\nThis Happy Moment\nTANT CHANNELS THOUSANDS OF MILES APART. BUT THE FAITH WITH\nIN THEMSELVES SUSTAINED EACH MEMBER OF THE FAMILY WHETHER\nTRAILS WERE IN LONESOME TOWNS AT HOME. OR AT A FARAWAY BAT\nTLE STATION. NOW, FAITH HAS SEEN THEM THROUGH TO FINAL AND\nCOMPLETE PEACE\nFrank Armstrong and Co.\n2912 Biddle Avenue\nK\n\nTHIS IS WHAT\nWE HAVE ALL\nWAITED FOR...\nGIVE THANKS\nTO THE MANY\nWHO BROUGHT\nTHIS VICTORY\nMM},,\n1\nHAILS THE REALIZATION OF\nOUR CONCEPT OF LIVING\nTHAT FREEDOM IS EVERY MAN'S\nHERITAGE.\nand the Star Spangled Banner in triumph\nshall wave o'er the land of the free\nand the home of the brave.\n\nJAGER\u2019S HARDWARE\n3050 FIRST STREET WYANDOTTE\n-J3\\\nV-J\nDAY\nInternational Law And Order\nAmong United Nations Peace Aims\nNow that the last gun has been\nfired in the greatest conflict the\nworld has ever faced, the larger\naim for which we fought still re\nmains, the aim to reduce interna\ntional anarchy to a regime of law\nand order and abolishment of war\nas the arbiter between nations.\nIn a recent address before the\nUnited States Senate, when he ad\nvocated adoption of the United Na\ntions Charter, Senator Homer Fer\nguson declared that the grand ob\njective of the present experiment in\ninternational organization is to try\nto conquer and wipe out world-wide\nlawlessness.\nCHARTER ATTEMPTS TO\nLIFT LEVEL OF LIFE\nCalling the charter objectives a\ndaring attempt to lift the level of\ncivilized life from the national to\nthe international plane, Ferguson\nsaid, \u201cReal peace is made only\nthrough the force of voluntarily ac\ncepted law and order, by good will,\nby cooperation in all areas of hu\nman endeavor. It depends upon the\nacceptance of principles of right\nconduct, and by their enforcement\nthrough appropriate agencies spon\nsored by the whole international\ncommunity of nations.\u201d\nLISTS CHARTER OBJECTIVES\nFerguson listed the six objectives\nof the United Nations charter as:\n1. We seek to bring the relations\nbetween Nations under a system of\nlaw. order and justice as distin\nguished from national selfishness,\ninternational anarchy and lawless\nforce.\n2. Two horrible and devastating\nwars, together with the fear of what\na third World War w-ould mean to\ncivilization, have given us the de\ntermination to outlaw war and ag\ngression, to preserve peace by force\nif need be; and to do this by the\nproperly organized power of the na\ntions as an International commun\nity.\nECONOMIC COOPERATION\nSUBSTITUTED FOR WAR\n3. We seek to substitute economic\ncooperation for economic warfare\noetween nations in the hope of re\nmoving some of the basic causes of\nwar; and with the further aim of\npromoting the welfare of all the\npeoples of the world.\n4. We intend to promote on a\nWe Give Thanks For The\nPeace Which Has C ome\nTo Thy Children Through\nout The World.\nm -iyiV\nDOWN RIVER FEDERAL\nSAVINGS AND LOAN\nASSOCIATION\nscale never before attempted, the\neducational, social and cultural re\nlations between peoples of the world\nin an effort to bring about better\nunderstanding and genuine good\nneighborliness among nations.\n5. We seek to establish by an In\nternational Court of Justice equal\njustice under law as an interna\ntional as well as a national institu\ntion.\n6. We are determined to join in\nestablishing a framework of inter\nnational institutions and agencies\n(political, economic and social) as\ninstruments necessary for coopera\ntion, peace, and justice between na\ntions.\nUnemployment\nto Follow Closing\nof War Contracts\nCancellation of Army and Navy\nwar contracts immediately following\nV-J day will result in unemploy\nment for an estimated 5,000,000\nworkers within 60 days of the end\nof the war, according to Govern\nment officials.\nIn the Detroit area, contract can\ncellations will probably result in\n250,000 to 300,000 men and women\nbeing released from their jobs in\nDetroit factories within a few\nweeks, R. J. Thomas, president of\nthe UAW-CIO, reported.\nArmy plans include cancellation\nfrom 80 to 90 per cent of its orders,\nThomas was informed after check\ning with agencies in Washington.\nWidespread cancellation of Navy\norders will also result, he added,\nalthough more of the Navy's pro\ngram will be continued.\nMost of the unemployment will\nbe temporary, government officials\npointed out, with its length depend\ning on the rapidity of industry to\nconvert to peacetime production. It\nwas stated that re-employment in\nthe automobile industry might pro\nceed fairly rapidly but there will\nbe many layoffs until automobile\nmanufacture hits its stride.\nBirds cannot see violets and blues\nvery well, according to the Better\nVision Institute. Some birds, how--\never, can perceive infra-red rays\ninvisible to human eyes.\nREPLACE CAUSEWAY ON\nSTILWELL ROAD\nOne of the most striking jobs re\ncently completed by the U. 6. En\ngineers on the Stilwell road was\nthe replacement of a deteriorated\ncauseway constructed by the Chin-\nto\n\u25a0R MIK\n\nj IH^Hw\n?*\"*k Sk\nA BRIGHT WORLD DAWNING\nIT\u2019S OF HIS MAKING... AND HE\nASKS SO LITTLE IN RETURN!\nThe man in uniform isn\u2019t looking backward to the battles he fought and\nthe tragedy he has seen. He\u2019s looking forward\u2014to the life of peace and\nsecurity with his family which his sacrifices were meant to secure. He's\nlooking forward to a good job and the opportunity for success which is\nevery American\u2019s birthright. And in his bright new world will be a richer\nunderstanding of those with whom he works\u2014of his neighbors\u2014of his\nchildren\u2019s schoolmates. Because \u2018\u2018out there\u201d under flying shells and flak\nhe learned to re-evaluate the simple joys of home \u2014of tolerance \u2014and of\nprayer. All he wants of us for whom he fought, are help in reestablishing\nhimself with his family; his old job back (or a better one); and the presenca\nof friends and loved ones.\nTHIS MESSAGE SPONSORED BY\nLYNCH SULLIVAN\nFURNITURE\n2955 BIDDLE AVENUE WYANDOTTE\nThe Guns Of Wa\nAre Still!\nIn this hour of victory we are ever thankful that our weapons\nhave found their mark have avenged the repulsive Jap atrocities.\nCivilized man will now make the Jap pay for his complete lack of\nregard for any hu\nman dignity or for\nany code of ethics\neven such as has\nbeen observed by\nother warring na\ntionse, since primi\ntive tribe battled\ntribe.\nWe salute our gal\nlant fighting men\nand women who\nhave brought us this\nday of Total Victory,\nThis Message Sponsored By\nEdwins Jew r elers\n3150 BIDDLE AVENUE Opp. Majestic Theatre\nTflt W X AiNUVJI iCi lUino-nLnAiiU v-j Luiiiun\nPAGE\nese just before last year\u2019s monsoon\nrains. A fill approximately two\nmiles long and 18 feet high, in-\nfj;., JK/mj' -EKti hHH^HBb\njjilHBBlIBIBBI^BEBraB^??^Jr\n\u00ab\u2014-I \u25a07\nBpr TO|\nsV\nkK>\". 4 W\" 1\"*-'\"' *rHW^* i \u00a3*\"#^i?l\nAUGUST 1945\nI volving 215,000 yards of earth am\n10.000 yards of gravel topping was\n1 placed in record time","height":"34374","width":"25827"}}
